221, \"to\": 232}, {\"ngram\": \"Spain\", \"from\": 236, \"to\": 241}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 296}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 309, \"to\": 332}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS PublishedJul 24, 2024, 07:50 PM UpdatedJul 26, 2024, 12:21 AM TAHITI-While most Olympians will be battling for glory in Paris, the world's best surfers will be going for gold some 16,000km away on the island of Tahiti, where the spinning blue barrels of Teahupo'o might be the real star of the show.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 670, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 360, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 491, \"end\": 496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7589648044948195e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 582, \"end\": 588, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 5.148440864898833e-12, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"PHOTO\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"07:50 PM UpdatedJul\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 410}, {\"ngram\": \"12:21 AM TAHITI\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"most Olympians\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"glory\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 484}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 542}, {\"ngram\": \"the island\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"the spinning blue barrels\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 631}, {\"ngram\": \"the real star\", \"from\": 641, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Competition is likely to be fierce between the sport's traditional powerhouses, but host nation France are a genuine threat after two Tahitian locals qualified to compete at their home break.\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 768, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.998817508905585, \"rank\": 0.0011675835116317964, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 814, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.704400669401022e-14, \"text\": \"Tahitian\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Competition\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport's traditional powerhouses\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"a genuine threat\", \"from\": 779, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"their home break\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Hosting the Olympics at Teahupo'o is the best spot they could ever pick just because it's such a good wave at that time of the year,\\\" said local Vahine Fierro, who won the Tahiti Pro in pumping waves in May.\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 1073, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 886}, {\"ngram\": \"the best spot\", \"from\": 903, \"to\": 916}, {\"ngram\": \"such a good wave\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 985}, {\"ngram\": \"the year\", \"from\": 989, \"to\": 997}, {\"ngram\": \"local Vahine Fierro\", \"from\": 1005, \"to\": 1024}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tahiti Pro\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"waves\", \"from\": 1060, \"to\": 1065}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 1069, \"to\": 1072}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Olympics are going back to where the surf was born.\\\"\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 1075, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"the surf\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1120}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Surfing was recorded in French Polynesia, now an overseas territory of France, as early as the 12th century but made its first Olympic appearance in Tokyo only in 2021.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1301, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1164, \"end\": 1173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.5835389605702996, \"rank\": 0.7136816349381049, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Polynesia\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.998817508905585, \"rank\": 0.0011675835116317964, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1282, \"end\": 1287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9994932875921312, \"rank\": 0.0005069689410751319, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Surfing\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"now an overseas territory\", \"from\": 1175, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"the 12th century\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1240}, {\"ngram\": \"its first Olympic appearance\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The surf contest in front of the idyllic lagoon-side village of Teahupo'o will bear little resemblance to Tokyo, let alone the exploits of those early wave riders.\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1409, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9994932875921312, \"rank\": 0.0005069689410751319, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The surf contest\", \"from\": 1303, \"to\": 1319}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1328}, {\"ngram\": \"the idyllic lagoon-side village\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1363}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"little resemblance\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1405}, {\"ngram\": \"the exploits\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1438}, {\"ngram\": \"those early wave riders\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Italo Ferreira and Carissa Moore carved and spun their way to gold in the murky, typhoon-churned waves of Japan's Shidashita beach, Teahupo'o breaks perfectly over a coral reef and is renowned for its heavy, hollow tubes.\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carissa Moore\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carissa_Moore\"}, {\"begin\": 1580, \"end\": 1585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9958741154371638, \"rank\": 0.0041346133645034, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Italo Ferreira\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1488}, {\"ngram\": \"their way\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1532}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1536, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"the murky, typhoon-churned waves\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1576}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1615}, {\"ngram\": \"a coral reef\", \"from\": 1638, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"its heavy, hollow tubes\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1694}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's a totally different wave,\\\" said Lucca Mesinas, who represented Peru in Tokyo and has also qualified for Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 1697, \"to\": 1818, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1735, \"end\": 1740, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucca\", \"score\": 0.9999998038156456, \"rank\": 1.7221762860984243e-07, \"text\": \"Lucca\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucca\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lucca\"}, {\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peru\", \"score\": 0.999999223910737, \"rank\": 7.760773728825385e-07, \"text\": \"Peru\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peru\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peru\"}, {\"begin\": 1774, \"end\": 1779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9994932875921312, \"rank\": 0.0005069689410751319, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1807, \"end\": 1817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.379336215156211e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a totally different wave\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1727}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Japan was a beach break and a lot of wind.\", \"from\": 1820, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9958741154371638, \"rank\": 0.0041346133645034, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a beach break\", \"from\": 1831, \"to\": 1844}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1849, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"wind\", \"from\": 1858, \"to\": 1862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was really hard waves to surf.\", \"from\": 1864, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hard waves\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tahiti is just an amazing island with a perfect lefthander.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Tahiti\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1906}, {\"ngram\": \"just an amazing island\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1932}, {\"ngram\": \"a perfect lefthander\", \"from\": 1938, \"to\": 1958}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It usually is barrelling, so it's a super nice wave.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a super nice wave\", \"from\": 1994, \"to\": 2011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It can be really big too, and it can be really strong.\\\"\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2068, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Teahupo'o, which translates as \\\"Pile of Heads\\\" after a gruesome local legend, was picked to stage the Olympic competition because the beaches in France are mostly flat this time of year.\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2256, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2215, \"end\": 2221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.998817508905585, \"rank\": 0.0011675835116317964, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2070, \"to\": 2079}, {\"ngram\": \"Pile\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2106}, {\"ngram\": \"Heads\", \"from\": 2110, \"to\": 2115}, {\"ngram\": \"a gruesome local legend\", \"from\": 2123, \"to\": 2146}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic competition\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2191}, {\"ngram\": \"the beaches\", \"from\": 2200, \"to\": 2211}, {\"ngram\": \"year\", \"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While the biggest waves rise about 10m and are not as tall as those in Portugal's Nazare or Hawaii's Peahi, the explosive power, giant tubes and sheer volume of water set Teahupo'o apart.\", \"from\": 2258, \"to\": 2445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2329, \"end\": 2337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"score\": 0.9998958916612241, \"rank\": 7.933849221170746e-05, \"text\": \"Portugal\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Portugal\"}, {\"begin\": 2350, \"end\": 2356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"score\": 0.999999998275598, \"rank\": 1.7246037876294221e-09, \"text\": \"Hawaii\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hawaii\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the biggest waves\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2281}, {\"ngram\": \"the explosive power\", \"from\": 2366, \"to\": 2385}, {\"ngram\": \"giant tubes\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2398}, {\"ngram\": \"sheer volume\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2415}, {\"ngram\": \"water\", \"from\": 2419, \"to\": 2424}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Huge storms in the South Pacific generate swells of 9-12m which travel thousands of kilometres before lurching out of deep water onto the shallow reef.\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2598, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Huge storms\", \"from\": 2447, \"to\": 2458}, {\"ngram\": \"the South Pacific generate swells\", \"from\": 2462, \"to\": 2495}, {\"ngram\": \"9-12m\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2504}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 2518, \"to\": 2527}, {\"ngram\": \"kilometres\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2541}, {\"ngram\": \"deep water\", \"from\": 2565, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"the shallow reef\", \"from\": 2581, \"to\": 2597}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A deep trench carved by fresh water running off the jungle-clad mountains provides an incredibly close and relatively safe spot for spectator boats, while judges will watch from a controversial new tower built into the reef itself.\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2831, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A deep trench\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2613}, {\"ngram\": \"fresh water\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2635}, {\"ngram\": \"the jungle-clad mountains\", \"from\": 2648, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"an incredibly close and relatively safe spot\", \"from\": 2683, \"to\": 2727}, {\"ngram\": \"spectator boats\", \"from\": 2732, \"to\": 2747}, {\"ngram\": \"judges\", \"from\": 2755, \"to\": 2761}, {\"ngram\": \"a controversial new tower\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2803}, {\"ngram\": \"the reef\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2823}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fierro believes the thrill of a successful wave at Teahupo'o is unmatchable.\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2909, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Fierro\", \"from\": 2833, \"to\": 2839}, {\"ngram\": \"the thrill\", \"from\": 2849, \"to\": 2859}, {\"ngram\": \"a successful wave\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2880}, {\"ngram\": \"Teahupo'o\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Paddling into a wave as hard as you can, not knowing if you are going to make the drop or not because it's so hollow, getting into this big blue tube that just feels like time is stopping.\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 3100, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a wave\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"the drop\", \"from\": 2990, \"to\": 2998}, {\"ngram\": \"this big blue tube\", \"from\": 3043, \"to\": 3061}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 3083, \"to\": 3087}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And then coming out with like the spit of the wave in the back, into the boats like that are right there - it's just indescr